    <h5 class="card-title">SAP Recruitment Process and Test Pattern:</h5>
      <p class="card-text">SAP Labs mainly hires candidates from on-campus drives and off-campus recruitments. The hiring process is given below.</p>

   <h5 class="card-title">SAP On-Campus Recruitment Process and Test Pattern:</h5>
    <p class="card-text">SAP conducts campus placement drives in several colleges. They place a lot of importance to leadership, communication and innovation skills. Try to develop these skills while in college and have proof that showcases these skills. You should meet the prerequisites mentioned in the eligibility criteria and the skills required.</p>

 <p class="card-text">After having these prerequisites, these are the following rounds that SAP conducts for the SAP on-campus recruitment process.</p>

<br><b>•	Online test-</b> The Online test in the SAP recruitment process consist of 25 aptitude questions and 2-3 coding questions. The online test is a screening round. Questions asked in the test are quantitative ability questions and logical reasoning questions, along with coding questions.

<br><b>•	Technical Interview- </b>The SAP recruitment process consists of 2 technical interview rounds. The technical interview questions are asked from subjects like SQL, C, C++, Java, Data Structures, Operating Systems etc.

<br><b>•	Managerial Interview-</b> There will be 1 managerial interview round in the SAP Recruitment Process. The managerial round questions are subjective opinions on current affairs. In this round, the interviewer is trying to assess the thinking process and hence you need to answer carefully.

<br><b>•	HR Interview-</b> The final round in the SAP Recruitment Process is the HR interview. This interview is to see if the candidate fits into the company culture. General HR questions will be asked to test your communication skills and work ethics.
    

 <h5 class="card-title">SAP Off-Campus Recruitment Process and Test Pattern</h5>
  <p class="card-text">The Off-campus recruitment process is spread across 3 rounds. These are:
	
<br><b>•	Online test-</b> The SAP Off-Campus Recruitment Process consists of an online test round. The online test consists of MCQ questions based on verbal ability and technical questions. 23 coding questions are also asked.

<br><b>•	Technical interviews-</b> The topics you have to concentrate on the technical interview for the SAP Off-Campus Recruitment Process are Java, Operating System, Coding etc.

<br><b>•	Managerial interview-</b>The Managerial interview in the SAP Off-Campus Recruitment Process is also technical in nature. For instance, the candidate would be asked to create an algorithm based on a given criteria.

<p>SAP accepts applications for SAP Off-Campus Recruitment Process from various portals. But the best way to turn the application to an offer is through a recommendation or referral. The other ways to apply are through their careers page or LinkedIn.</p>

  
